'''European Working Group on Libre Software'''

URL = http://eu.conecta.it/


=Description=

The working group on libre software was created at the initiative of the Information Society Directorate General, with the purpose to analyze the free software phenomenon, create a set of recommendations for the Community and create a paper to be presented to the Commission.

The group featured both people from the Commission and representative members from the EU countries.


=More Information=

Cordis has prepared a page with Free/Open source activities in European programmes, available at http://www.cordis.lu/ist/ka4/tesss/impl_free.htm.
Many additional informations can also be found at the IDA (Interchange of Data between Administrations) homepage, at http://europa.eu.int/ISPO/ida

For information request you can e-mail to cdaffara@conecta.it.


